<h2> Introduction:</h2>
This lab provides experience with file I/O.
<h2> Lab Assignment:</h2>

<h4> Problem Motivation and Definition:</h4>

This lab is intended to provide experience with text file I/O.<p>
We want to write a program which will behave like the Unix <b>wc</b>
utility.

<h4> Solution Specification:</h4>
<ol>
<ol>
<li>
Create a new directory, <i>lab10</i>, and move to it.</li>

<li>
Copy <tt>~cs201300/lab10/HappyFunBall.txt</tt> to your lab10 directory.
</li>

<li>
Combining the functionality of programs 7-11 and 7-12 in Forouzan, write a
program which counts <u>characters</u>, <u>words</u>, and <u>lines</u>
of a file and then writes the totals to standard output.
</li>

<li>
Use the <tt>HappyFunBall.txt</tt> file as your input file (do not read it from
standard input).
</li>

<li>
Compare your results with those of the Unix <b>wc</b> command run on the same file.
</li>

<li>
When correct, generate a printout of the source, and demonstrate, via
typescript, the source and the running of the program data.
</li>

</ol>


